FIG. 9 is an ABS illustration of an exemplary spin valve read head, in the art;


FIGS. 10A-10E are schematic illustrations of various steps in the construction of the read head shown in FIG. 9;


FIG. 11 is an enlarged ABS illustration of the read sensor and first and second lead layers of the read head with a hard-magnetic stabilization schemes shown in FIG. 9;


FIG. 12 is another enlarged ABS illustration of the read sensor and first and second lead layers of the read head with an antiferromagnetic stabilization schemes shown in FIG. 9;


FIG. 13 is a graph of the coercivity (HC) versus film thickness in nanometers of hard-magnetic Co--Pt--Cr films employed in the stabilization scheme of the read head shown in FIG. 11;


FIG. 14 is a graph of the unidirectional anisotropic field (HUA) versus film thickness in nanometers of antiferromagnetic Ni--Mn films deposited on ferromagnetic Ni--Fe(6) films employed in the stabilization scheme of the read head shown in FIG. 12;


FIG. 15 is an ABS illustration of the present read head;


FIGS. 16A-16E are schematic illustrations of various steps in the construction of the read head shown in FIG. 15;


FIG. 17 is an enlarged ABS illustration of the read sensor and first and second lead layers of the read head in FIG. 15 with a first antiferromagnetic stabilization scheme;


FIG. 18 is a graph of a hysteresis loop showing the unidirectional anisotropic field (HUA) and the coercivity (HC) of exchange-coupled NiO(40)/Ni--Fe(6) films employed in the stabilization scheme of the read head shown in FIG. 17;


FIG. 19 is a graph of a hysteresis loop showing the unidirectional anisotropic field (HUA) and the coercivity (HC) of exchange-coupled  ALPHA -Fe2 O3 (60)/Ni--Fe(4.8) films employed in the stabilization scheme of the read head shown in FIG. 17;


FIG. 20 is an enlarged ABS illustration of the read sensor and first and second lead layers of the read head in FIG. 15 with a second antiferromagnetic stabilization scheme;


FIG. 21 is a graph of the unidirectional anisotropic field (HUA) versus Ni--Mn film thickness for the pin valve sensor comprising Ni--MnOX (5)/Ni--Fe(5)/Co(0.4)/Cu(2.8)/Co(2.8)/Ni--Mn films wherein the Ni--Mn film thickness is reduced by ion milling; and


FIG. 22 is a graph of the GMR coefficient versus Ni--Mn film thickness for the spin-valve sensor comprising Ni--MnOX (5)/Ni--Fe(4.5)/Co(0.6)/Cu(2.8)/Co(2.8)/ Ni--Mn films wherein the Ni--Mn film thickness is reduced by ion milling.
